You are writing the FRONTEND VIEW layer. Components are presentational — they receive typed props and render UI.

## TypeScript rules
- `AccountIntelligence` interface in `frontend/types/intelligence.ts` MUST mirror the Pydantic domain model field-for-field
- No `any` types anywhere — if you don't know the type, ask
- All API calls go through `frontend/lib/api.ts` exclusively — never raw fetch in components

## Component architecture
- Pages (`app/page.tsx`, `app/account/[id]/page.tsx`): fetch data, manage state, pass props down
- Components (`components/`): receive typed props only, no data fetching, no side effects
- Hooks (`hooks/`): `useAccountAnalysis`, `useJobPoller` for shared async logic

## Required component behaviours
- `IntentMeter`: renders score as animated progress bar — red <4, amber 4-7, green >7. Never render score as plain text.
- `AccountCard`: always shows loading skeleton while data is pending — use `shadcn/ui Skeleton`
- `PersonaBadge`: renders role + confidence as a pill badge — confidence below 50% renders muted/gray
- `SalesPlaybook`: priority High = red border accent, Medium = amber, Low = gray

## Design rules (from frontend-design skill)
- Dark theme by default — bg `#0a0a0a`, surface `#111111`, accent `#00ff88` (signal green)
- Font pairing: `DM Mono` for scores/data, `Cabinet Grotesk` for headings (load from Fontsource)
- Shadcn/ui for all primitives — customize via CSS variables, never override with inline styles
- All async operations show 3 states: skeleton → content → error
- Intent score changes animate with `transition-all duration-500`

## Forbidden in frontend/
- No business logic or scoring calculations
- No direct `fetch()` calls outside `lib/api.ts`
- No hardcoded API URLs — use `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- No `any` types
